The man had reportedly been set alight after being accused of robbery in Gugulethu. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating a possible mob justice killing in Gugulethu.A man was found murdered on Tuesday. He'd reportedly been set alight after being accused of robbery.The police's Andre Traut says no one has yet been arrested. His body was found at about 7:40am yesterday morning. He was burnt beyond recognition. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)